ABSTRACT OF JUDGMENT
THE STATE OF TEXAS
COUNTY OF TRAVIS
On February 10, 2022, the County Court at Law No. 3 of Bexar County, Texas, in a case entitled Vermeer
Great Plains, INC vs. Valero Construction, LLC d/b/a Valero Horizontal Drilling, Cause No. 2021CV04144 on the
docket of the Court, rendered judgment in favor of Vermeer Great Plains, INC and against Valero Construction,
LLC d/b/a Valero Horizontal Drilling, the details of which are as follows:
1. The name and address of the judgment creditor is Vermeer Great Plains, INC, in care of Barnett &
Garcia, P.L.L.C ., 3821 Juniper Trace, Suite 108, Austin, Texas 78738.
2. The name, address and telephone number of the attorney for the judgment creditor is Matias Eduardo
Garcia, Barnett & Garcia, P.L.L.C ., 3821 Juniper Trace, Suite 108, Austin, Texas 78738, (512) 266-8830.
3. The name and address of the judgment is as follows:
Valero Construction, LLC d/b/a Valero Horizontal Drilling, 3618 Puesta de Sol, San Antonio, TX
78261.
4. The judgment was rendered for the principal amount of $51,135.91, interest in the amount of $1,870.31,
attorney's fees in the amount of $1,200.00, and costs of $392.95, for a total judgment of $54,599.17.
5. The rate of interest specified in the judgment is five percent (5%) per annum on the entire amount of the
judgment from the date of judgment.
Signed this 28 th day of June, 2022.
ATTORNEY FOR PLAINTIFF
VERMEER GREAT PLAINS, INC
MATIAS EDUARDO GARCIA
BEFORE ME, the undersigned authority, on this 2 8 7 day of June, 2022, personally appeared Matias
Eduardo Garcia, who, being by me duly sworn, on oath stated that the information in the foregoing abstract of
judgment is within his personal knowledge and true and correct.
AFTER RECORDING, RETURN TO:
AA51737.001
MATIAS EDUARDO GARCIA
Barnett & Garcia, P.L.L ., C.
3821 Juniper Trace, Suite 108
Austin, Texas 78738
Sieg linde & deixando
Notary Public, State of Texas
SIEGLINDE ELAINE ALEXANDER
Notary ID #132568915
My Commission Expires
July 14, 2024
